HANTAVIRUIS PULMONARY SYNDROME, UPDATE: JUNE 1996
=================================================
From: "Pflieger, Anne K." <aap4@CIDDVD1.EM.CDC.GOV>
Date: Fri, 21 Jun 96 09:38:00 EST

Since HPS was first recognized in May 1993, 139 laboratory confirmed cases
have been added to the national registry maintained by CDC. Of the 139
total cases, 38 cases were identified retrospectively, with an onset of
illness prior to May 1993. Twenty-three confirmed cases occurred in 1995;
and to date, six cases with onset of illness in 1996 have been added.
Cumulative descriptive demographic statistics for the 139 confirmed cases
(from 25 states) in the HPS registry:
GENDER Frequency Percent
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
MALE 81 58.3
FEMALE 58 41.7

RACE Frequency Percent
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
WHITE 100 71.9
BLACK 3 2.2
AMERICAN INDIAN 36 25.9

ETHNICITY Frequency Percent
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
HISPANIC 16 11.5

CASE FATALITY Frequency Percent
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
DIED 70 50.4

AGE (yrs)
--------------
Mean = 36
Minimum = 11
Maximum = 69

